HEADWORD: Pimiento
<hw>Pi*mien"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.]</ety>
<def>The Spanish sweet pepper, the fruit of which is used as a
vegetable, to stuff olives, etc.; also the fruit itself. Also called
